Cell[TextData[{
 "Finally, in the paper they also provide analytical computations for the ",
 StyleBox["symplectic eigenvalues ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " from ",
 StyleBox["the \[ScriptCapitalS]-transform.",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " We omit that part here and show only the numerics. Nevertheless, this \
computation is useful be cause \n\ni) it immediately provides an energy upper \
bound for the CM, and\n\nii) also provides insight in any quantities which \
might depend on them.\n\nSee a review on: https://arxiv.org/pdf/2106.11965. \n\
\n- A pedagogical tutorial on symplectic eigenvalues ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Nu]", "i"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "5fd47595-ec75-4dfb-9d8f-f10363f0a41a"],
 " and derivations can be found here: \
https://markwilde.com/teaching/2019-spring-gqi/scribe-notes/lecture-10-\
scribed.pdf"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9414778823113203`*^9, 3.941478002824271*^9}, {
  3.9414786777645073`*^9, 3.94147868091678*^9}, {3.941478836501719*^9, 
  3.941478852488491*^9}, {3.941479008942635*^9, 
  3.941479011695478*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"68c19b76-a6a7-4bc8-8547-\
83efce097009"],

